            g.nodes.Add(new DialogueNode { id = "cal_read", speaker = "Calloway", text = "*(He holds still under your sense — and here is the first surprising thing: he *lets* you, fully, with the easy confidence of a man who has nothing hidden because he hides nothing, only *prices* it.)* *(And your sense finds two things at once, both wholly true, refusing to resolve into one. The first is the harm, plain and real: a soul that treats other souls as *currency*, that has, with genuine relish, built a fortune on the desperation of the discarded — the ones with nowhere else to go, whom he meets at their lowest and sells, at interest, the dignity the gods denied them for free. He owns pieces of a hundred souls. He would, your sense reads without doubt, broker the Wall, the world, you, anything, if the margin pleased him. There is no cruelty in it — that is almost the worst part — only *appetite*, vast and amused and utterly without remorse. And the second thing, underneath, is the part that makes him magnificent rather than merely monstrous: a courage. Your sense reads the soul he was — discarded, like all of them, godless, unclaimed, thrown toward the Wall to dissolve into the nothing — and reads the precise moment, somewhere in the cold, that Calloway looked at a cosmos which had weighed him and found him worth *nothing*, and made a decision so audacious it rewrote him: he decided he would simply *disagree.* That if no god would claim him, he would *claim himself*, and set his own price, and make it *exorbitant.* He refused — the only soul in all the grey you have met who flatly, gleefully *refused* — to be small, to be sad, to be grateful for scraps, to grieve. He looked at the Wall of the Faithless and threw a *party.* And your sense reads the thing he would never say and you will never prove: that the whole gorgeous machine of him — the coat, the house, the bottomless charm, the fortune in mortgaged souls — is a *cathedral* built to a single defiant article of faith, that a soul no god wanted is not worth *nothing*, but worth *whatever it has the nerve to charge* — and that he believes this so completely, and lives it so well, that he has become, in a country full of grieving gods and weeping dead, the one genuinely *free* thing in it. He is a predator. He is also the only soul here who is not afraid. Your sense cannot make those into one fact, because they aren't one; they are both, entire, and that — you understand, watching him watch you understand it — is the whole and exact reason he is impossible to hate.)*", onEnter = new[] { new FlagClause { key = "cal.read", op = FlagOp.SetTrue }, new FlagClause { key = "cal.knows_the_refusal", op = FlagOp.SetTrue } } });
            g.nodes.Add(new DialogueNode { id = "cal_pitch", speaker = "Calloway", text = "*(He spreads his hands to take in the warm, loud, impossible room.)* …*this*, cold one, is the *Long* *Odds.* …the *one* *establishment* in all the *land* of the *dead* …where a *discarded* *soul* can still get a *deal.* *(he ticks it off, fond)* …*borrow* against your *afterlife.* *wager* your *fate.* *sell* a *memory* you'd rather not *keep* — i pay *top* *coin* for a *good* *regret.* *buy* a *favor*, a *door*, a *day.* …and *what* am *i?* *(he grins)* …i'm the *house.* i'm the *man* who *noticed*, friend, what *no* one *else* in this *grey* *swindle* had the *stomach* to *say* *out* *loud*: that *death* *changed* *nothing.* …there's still the *haves* and the *have*-*nots*, still *power* and *want*, still *marks* and *players* — the *gods* just *dress* it up in *judgment* and *call* it *justice.* …*i* *don't* *dress* it up. *(he taps the felt)* …*here*, it's *honest.* the *odds* are *posted.* the *house* *edge* is *printed* on the *wall.* i *tell* you, to your *face*, that i mean to *win* — and i *never*, *ever* *lie*, because a *lie* is a *debt* you take *out* against your *own* *credibility*, and i am *far* too *rich* to *borrow.* …*(softly, and it is the truest thing he's said)* …the *gods* threw you in a *wall* …for *free*, cold one. *i'm* the *only* *soul* in *creation* …who'll *pay* you …for *being* *worth* *something.* …*tell* me again …*which* of *us* …is the *villain.*", onEnter = new[] { new FlagClause { key = "cal.asked_pitch", op = FlagOp.SetTrue }, new FlagClause { key = "cal.knows_the_house", op = FlagOp.SetTrue }, new FlagClause { key = "disp.heretical", op = FlagOp.AddInt, amount = 1 } } });
            g.nodes.Add(new DialogueNode { id = "cal_deal", speaker = "Calloway", text = "*(He sits up, *thrilled* — this is plainly his favorite part — and produces, from nowhere, a single blank marker of bone-white chip.)* …*oh*, i thought you'd *never* *ask.* *(he sets the marker on the felt between you)* …*here's* my *offer*, cold one, and i'll lay it *bare*, every *card* *face*-*up*, because i *never* *lie* and the *truth* is the *finest* *bait* there *is*: …*one* *marker.* a *favor*, redeemable *now* or *later*, *no* *questions* — and a *Returned's* *road* is *long* and *locked*, friend, you *will* hit a *door* you *cannot* *open*, and *this* *little* *chip* *opens* it. *that's* *real.* *that's* *yours.* …the *cost?* …*(he smiles, and it is genuinely, helpfully warm)* …*you* owe *me* *one.* *unspecified.* called in at a *time* of *my* *choosing.* …*now* — *(he leans back)* …a *smart* *soul* hears *'unspecified'* and *'my* *choosing'* and feels the *hook*, and a smart soul is *right* to. so *here's* what *you* do, cold one: you *haggle.* you *push*. you try to *pin* me down, *narrow* the *terms*, *read* the *snake* before you *shake* its *hand.* …*go* on. …*it's* the *only* part of the *game* …*i* *like* *better* …than *winning.*",
